The acts of this saint have the special interest for

us that they are extremely well authenticated. We have the sworn testimony of 249 juridical witnesses as to the facts of his life. These witnesses were ’ summoned for the process for his canonization‚ which was begun in 1330, under Pope John XXII„ twenty- seven years after his death.
